#Text=Reports of at least fourteen dead this week due to gun-related suicides in the United States
#Text=Correction — February 6 , 2013
#Text=This article does not conform to our neutrality policy , due to its manner of presentation of an out-of-context selection of facts .
#Text=The lapse appears to have been unintentional by all parties involved .
#Text=We apologize for the error .
#Text=Sunday , February 3 , 2013

#Text=A number of suicides as a result of self-inflicted gunshot wounds took place around the United States this week with reports of deaths in Arizona , California , Indiana , Maryland , New Jersey , New York , Nevada , Ohio , South Carolina and Washington .
#Text=Last Saturday in Mt . Pleasant , South Carolina , Assistant U.S. Attorney Alston Badger died from a self-inflicted gunshot wound .
#Text=He was 51 years old .
#Text=On Monday in Clark County , Nevada , Jody Sherman , the Ecomom founder and CEO , died from a self-inflicted gunshot wound .
#Text=Another suicide occurred Monday in New Jersey .
#Text=Chester and Rosaria Andraka died after Chester allegedly shot Rosaria before killing himself .
#Text=Chester was a former police officer and there were few signs of trouble in the relationship prior to their deaths .
#Text=Another murder-suicide shooting took place on Monday .
#Text=This one occurred in Elmont , New York , where 58-year-old Audley Dennis is believed to have shot his 46-year-old wife , Karen Rodgers-Dennis , before he shot himself .
#Text=The couple allegedly had a history of fighting , with a family friend telling the New York Post , “ They had their altercations .
#Text=They would argue and yell , have outbursts . "
